    <body>
      <entry xml:id="entry_lakʼon" xml:lang="os-x-iron">
        <form type="lemma"><orth>lakʼon</orth></form>
        <usg><lang/></usg>
        <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q>жидкая грязь</q>
            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
              <q>liquid dirt</q>
            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q>муть</q>
            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
              <q>mud</q>
            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q>мутный</q>
            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
              <q>muddy</q>
            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
        <abv:exampleGrp>
          <abv:example>
            <quote>don lakʼon ma kæn</quote>
            <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q>не мути воду</q>
            </abv:tr>
            <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
              <q>don't muddy the water</q>
            </abv:tr>
          </abv:example>
          <abv:example>
            <quote>Lewaxi æmvætænæj racydīs lakʼonæj</quote>
            <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q>(река) Лиахва во всю ширину понеслась мутная</q>
            </abv:tr>
            <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
              <q>(the river) Liakhvi ran muddy along full width</q>
            </abv:tr>
            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_F."/><biblScope>VI 37</biblScope></bibl>
          </abv:example>
        </abv:exampleGrp>
        <etym xml:lang="ru">В словах <oRef/> и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lækʼun"><mentioned
              xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/>
              <w>lækʼun</w></mentioned></ref> распознается один и тот же элемент <m>lak-</m>,
          который сопоставляется, с одной стороны, с <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
            <w>lakka</w>
            <gloss><q>пятно</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
            <w>laka</w>
            <gloss><q>пятно</q></gloss></mentioned>, с другой — <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><lang/>
            <w>lʼak</w>
            <gloss><q>грязный</q></gloss></mentioned> (из тюрк.?). В <oRef/> имеем в этом случае
            <m>lak</m> с осетинским фор­мантом <mentioned xml:lang="os"><m>-on</m></mentioned>, а в
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lækʼun"/> (из <w>læk-gun</w>) — формант <mentioned
            xml:lang="os-x-digor"><w>-gun</w></mentioned>.</etym>
        <etym xml:lang="en">In the words <oRef/> and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lækʼun"
              ><mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/>
              <w>lækʼun</w></mentioned></ref> one may recognize the same element <m>lak-</m>, which
          may be compared, on the one hand, with <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
            <w>lakka</w>
            <gloss><q>stain</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
            <w>laka</w>
            <gloss><q>stain</q></gloss></mentioned>, on the other — with <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><lang/>
            <w>lʼak</w>
            <gloss><q>dirty</q></gloss></mentioned> (from Turkic?). If so, in <oRef/> we find
            <m>lak</m> with the Ossetic formative <mentioned xml:lang="os"><m>-on</m></mentioned>,
          and in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lækʼun"/> (from <w>læk-gun</w>) — the formative
            <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><w>-gun</w></mentioned>.</etym>
      </entry>
